    "The random algorithm serves as a straightforward and unbiased baseline for comparison.",
    "It generates solutions randomly within the given input space without applying any optimization or learning strategies.",
    "The use of a random algorithm is standard practice in evaluating the effectiveness of more sophisticated algorithms because it helps to establish a minimum performance threshold.",
    "By comparing against a random search, we can assess whether the proposed methods (GA and RL-based approaches) provide significant improvements in both search efficiency and solution quality.",
    "If the advanced algorithms perform similarly or worse than the random baseline, it would indicate that they are not effectively exploring the solution space and might need further refinement."
